Object Oriented Programming(OOPs)
    OOPs is just a style of programming.(simple rules on how to write large amount of codes easily)
    it helps us manage and change large amounts of code. there are other ways as well
    like functional programming and procedural programming.

pillar of OOPs:
    there are four main pillars of OOPs.
    1)inheritance
    2)polymorphism
    3)abstraction
    4)encapsulation

classes and objects
    a class is a template/design/map/idea/blueprint from which objects are created

